{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "write batch accumulating writes before commit", "note": "pinned pebble.Batch at batch.go:240 and Commit/Close/Apply lines I cited in Task 1"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "pebble.Batch (direction=callers)", "note": "composed_by gave the exact direct-holder list I cited: indexedBatch batch.go:488, batchIter batch.go:1761, commitQueue commit.go:25, iteratorBatchState iterator.go:392, metamorphic/test.go:47, replay/replay.go:621"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "retained_via_interfaces produced the candidate spine of the whole audit — wal/failover_writer.go:25 and :31 RefCount rows, ConcurrencyLimitScheduler compaction_scheduler.go:260, rangeKeyMasking→SpanMask/BoundLimitedBlockPropertyFilter (internal/keyspan/interleaving_iter.go:226, scan_internal.go:226, sstable/block_property.go:638), invalidating/iterv2/keyspan InterleavingIter, bench.ycsb bench/ycsb.go:184 — all of which I confirmed at source and cited"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "record.Writer 'flusher' row (record/record.go:673) with chain bench.pebbleDB > pebble.DB > ... > Batch was spurious — the field is a file flusher; I rejected it after reading record/record.go:668-678"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "compact.Iter row named carrier pebble.batchIter; the real carrier on the flush path is flushableBatchIter over flushableBatch.data (compaction.go:1074), not batchIter"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "keyspan.SpanIterOptions.BlockPropertyFilter (internal/keyspan/iter.go:83) had no findable injection site of rangeKeyMasking; I could only rule it out by absence"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "missed entirely the biggest retainer: flushableEntry.flushable (flushable.go:71) holding *flushableBatch that aliases batch.data — I found it only by grepping newFlushableBatch callers"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "also missed mergingIterLevel.iter (merging_iter.go:25), mergingIterV2Level.iter (merging_iter_v2.go:222), and keyspanimpl.mergingIterLevel.iter (internal/keyspan/keyspanimpl/merging_iter.go:339), all confirmed indirect retainers"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no injection sites — every retained_via_interfaces row said 'which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified', so I had to grep WriteRecord( to find db.go:908/950 and read wal/failover_writer.go:150-185 to prove the *Batch actually lands in refCount"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no flushable/flushableEntry chain at all; grep for newFlushableBatch( and 'type flushableEntry struct' recovered db.go:832, db.go:2679-2683, db.go:2826, recovery.go:620-628"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no assignment sites for rangeKeyMasking; grep rangeKeyMasking + reading db.go:1290-1400 gave db.go:1312, db.go:1377, range_keys.go:575, external_iterator.go:290"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "read", "missing": "nothing about the V2 iterator stack; reading db.go:1505-1620 produced iterv2.InterleavingIter.Init at db.go:1578 and bld.AddLevel at db.go:1583/1685"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no goroutine-boundary information; Task 3 required grepping 'go ' to prove compaction.go:1389, compaction_scheduler.go:306, record/log_writer.go:595, wal/failover_manager.go:335"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "pebble.Batch (direction=callers)", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "call sites without snippets for most rows; grep for 'batchIter{' gave the four construction sites batch.go:1380/1386/1450/1524"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_graph pebble.Batch direction=callers depth=1", "query_after": "sense_blast pebble.Batch max_hops=4", "hint": "next_steps: '67 callers found — check blast radius before changing this symbol' — plus CLAUDE.md's retained_via_interfaces pointer, which is what made blast the Task 2 tool rather than more graph queries"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "query_before": "trusting retained_via_interfaces rows as findings", "query_after": "grep/read every injection site before stating a row", "hint": "retained_note: 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' and index_caveat about method-on-field dispatch — this directly set the confirmed/unconfirmed evidence labels in my answer"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "sense_blast's retained_via_interfaces list: 14 abstraction-boundary retention candidates with the containment chain spelled out (e.g. rangeKeyMasking > Iterator > iteratorBatchState > Batch, and *Batch-as-wal.RefCount) — that is exactly the class the team said a field-type sweep cannot see, and I would not have thought to look at wal/failover_writer.go or compaction_scheduler.go from grep alone.",
  "q5_improve": "Give each retained_via_interfaces row the assignment site, not just the field and a satisfier: the file:line where a concrete value is written into that interface field (db.go:950 for the RefCount, compaction_scheduler.go:304 for DBForCompaction). That is the single thing I had to grep for on every one of the 14 rows, and its absence is also why the biggest retainer — flushableEntry.flushable at flushable.go:71 — never appeared at all.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "Q1 shows sense_blast handed me the WAL-failover, scheduler, and range-key-masking retainers I could not have enumerated by grepping a type name, but Q1's misses (flushableEntry, the merging-iter levels) and Q2's six grep/read fallbacks to pin every injection site and every goroutine boundary mean it accelerated the audit without being able to finish it."
}

